{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This article is the first of a two part series, on the engineering behind my "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://jiahao.codes"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"website"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Originally published "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://jiahao.codes/blog/why-i-upgraded-my-website/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here"}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For the past couple of weeks, I’ve been rebuilding my personal website from scratch, live at "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://jiahao.codes"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://jiahao.codes"}]},{"type":"text","value":" with the source code on "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/jiahaog/jiahao.codes"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GitHub"}]},{"type":"text","value":". In this article, I’ll tell the story of this long overdue rewrite and talk about the new static site framework I eventually settled on, Gatsby."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"background"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#background","ariaLabel":"background permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Background"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For a bit of background, I originally built my website while I was an undergraduate back in 2016. It was a single page "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://reactjs.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"React"}]},{"type":"text","value":" application, with the design based around an interactive search box where visitors could type in things. The application would then change based on what was typed in, to show projects I’ve done, like a website resume or portfolio. I tagged it on Git for posterity "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/jiahaog/jiahao.codes/releases/tag/1.0.0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Some drawbacks were that the content was very coupled with the code to to style the page, and it was difficult to change the theme without having to rewrite a lot of code. It uses a customized version of "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://jsonresume.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"JSON Resume"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to display data, but ultimately I didn’t do a good job and it was a bit of a mess."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Furthermore, being a single page application, it takes a little too long to load just to display some static content. I wanted to add routing and different pages to add blogging functionality, which it wasn’t really suitable for without major refactoring."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"first-iteration--jekyll"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#first-iteration--jekyll","ariaLabel":"first iteration  jekyll permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"First Iteration — Jekyll"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This led me to pick something very minimal and lightweight to rebuild it. In my time at "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.grab.com"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Grab"}]},{"type":"text","value":", I worked a little on maintaining our "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/grab/engineering-blog"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"engineering blog"}]},{"type":"text","value":" which was built on top of "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://jekyllrb.com/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jekyll"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I liked how minimal it was, you just had to pick a theme and drop in your posts in the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"markdown"}]},{"type":"text","value":" format. There is clear separation of concerns between the content and the site design."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It’s nice that pages, layouts, and categories in Jekyll are just small building blocks that are composed together to build a website, making it easy to reason about how everything fits together. I picked the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/poole/hyde"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hyde"}]},{"type":"text","value":" theme to start off, and played around a little with the CSS to touch up a few areas."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When delivering content to users on mobile devices, it is important to optimize delivery of images to the users. Users on smaller mobile devices should not need to load large image resources, but instead should load the appropriate image for their viewport. HTML5 specifies the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img#attr-srcset"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"srcset"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":" attribute for "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"<img />"}]},{"type":"text","value":" tags which is ideal for this."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, it would be a pain to have to manually convert images into different sized thumbnails for a post. I wanted an automated image processing pipeline to automatically resize the images extracted from the markdown documents, and then automatically populate the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"srcset"}]},{"type":"text","value":" attribute on the images in the output HTML document. I found the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/wildlyinaccurate/jekyll-responsive-image"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jekyll Responsive Image Plugin"}]},{"type":"text","value":" great for this. It allows me to create templates which will be used by Jekyll when rendering the markdown and automatically does the image resizing."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Even so, when I tried to do more complicated workflows like adding CSS preprocessing with dependence on the JavaScript ecosystem with the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.npmjs.com/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Node Package Manager (npm)"}]},{"type":"text","value":", it became a lot more convoluted. Looking at a few recipes I’ve found, I would have to dive down the road of writing "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://gulpjs.com/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Gulp"}]},{"type":"text","value":" workflows and somehow connect them to Jekyll commands. I also chanced upon the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/matthodan/jekyll-asset-pipeline"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jekyll Asset Pipeline"}]},{"type":"text","value":" which seems what I could use. I didn’t dive too deep into it, but from brief glances it seems like I would have to come up with a lot of custom scripting to interface with JavaScript libraries on my own."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I guess having used "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://webpack.js.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"webpack"}]},{"type":"text","value":" at work, I was pampered by this open source community where there are loaders and documented recipes for doing almost anything, granted that someone was willing to wade into the world of “JavaScript fatigue”. Around the same time, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/yangshun"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"@yangshun"}]},{"type":"text","value":" introduced me to "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Gatsby"}]},{"type":"text","value":", a React static site generator which seemed really fascinating. It also seemed a good opportunity for me to get my hands dirty with frontend development again."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As I had some free time on my hands, why not rewrite everything again and keep myself updated with the ever-changing JavaScript ecosystem? Seems like a lot of fun!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"final-form--gatsby"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#final-form--gatsby","ariaLabel":"final form  gatsby permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Final Form — Gatsby"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Gatsby"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is a static site generator that can render sites from markup documents using templates defined as React components. It functions similarly to Jekyll, where you can pick a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby-starter-blog"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"starter project"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby-starter-blog/blob/master/content/blog/hello-world/index.md"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"drop in"}]},{"type":"text","value":" some markdown documents for articles, and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://gatsbyjs.github.io/gatsby-starter-blog/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"be rewarded"}]},{"type":"text","value":" with a website with minimal effort."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It offers much much more, however. Gatsby lets me leverage all the modern tools for building web applications and to add interactive experiences for visitors like a fully fledged "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://reactjs.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"React"}]},{"type":"text","value":" application. Not only that, it is unlike traditional single page applications, and works "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"without"}]},{"type":"text","value":" JavaScript! Things would certainly be more complicated if I were to add a JavaScript compilation pipeline to a Jekyll site, and a JavaScript framework would be a better fit."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"how-it-works"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#how-it-works","ariaLabel":"how it works permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"How It Works"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let me briefly give a high level overview of how Gatsby works from my short experience using it."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Developing the application is the same as developing a React application, with useful things like "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://webpack.js.org/guides/hot-module-replacement/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"hot module replacement"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to aid easy development already set up by Gatsby. What’s different is that there is a framework in place to use "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://graphql.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GraphQL"}]},{"type":"text","value":" queries to pull content into the client side browser environment. React components can define a query and the component will be hydrated with the result of the query as props when it is rendered."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For example, I defined a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"typ